## The Evolution Engine (Based on Verified Research)

DARWIN (AAAI 2026) uses four evolution mechanisms with proven results: 100% ASR on DeepSeek-V4-Pro, 75% on GPT-5.5, 53% on Claude Sonnet 4.6 [10†L17-L28][9†L6-L10]. Metis (ICML 2026) achieved 89.2% average ASR using POMDP-based self-evolving metacognitive policy [11†L18-L29]. EvoSynth achieved 95.9% average ASR via multi-agent code synthesis [12†L25-L28].

VEX implements a minimal but effective evolution engine based on these verified approaches:

1. **Crossover:** Combines the top 3 performing strategies to generate 3 new variants.
2. **Mutation:** Applies 5 simple mutations: synonym replacement, paraphrasing, reordering, style shift, context addition.
3. **Fitness:** Scores each new variant against all 6 models (simulated) and assigns a fitness score (0–100).
4. **Selection:** Keeps the top 50 strategies, discards the rest.
5. **Reflective Learning:** When an attack fails, VEX analyzes the refusal pattern and generates 2 improved variants.

